node.text:
New York In Bloom – a project put together by photographer Melanie Dunea.
 
New York In Bloom highlights the beauty and color that still exists in New York City while so many lives have been put on pause.
 
Melanie has put out a trio of limited edition silk scarves based on photographs she took of the city over the last few months.
 
The pieces function as wearable art and can be used as traditional scarves, face coverings, or even framed on a wall to show off their full beauty.
 
The collection can be seen at MelanieDunea.com, with a portion of the proceeds going to the NYC COVID-19 Response & Impact Fund.
